      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 865: `conv-\u003ereinvitePending` is an in-memory flag that determines whether a removed conversation is resurrected after clone success. If the daemon restarts after accepting the re-invitation but before `handlePendingConversation()` runs, the persisted tombstone remains and the clone completion path cannot distinguish an accepted re-invitation from a local removal. This can leave the accepted conversation removed even though the clone succeeded. Consider persisting an explicit pending-reinvite state, or clearing/retaining the invitation so the operation can be retried safely after restart.",
