      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 1510: Accepting a re-invitation for a removed conversation only sets `reinvitePending`, but it does not refresh the stored `ConvInfo` fields from the new request. If the previous tombstone has stale `members`, `mode`, or `created` values, `handlePendingConversation()` later persists that stale metadata when clearing `removed/erased`. At minimum, mirror the new-conversation initialization for request-derived fields while still leaving `removed/erased` intact until clone success.\n```suggestion\n    } else if (conv-\u003einfo.isRemoved()) {\n        conv-\u003einfo.created \u003d request.received;\n        conv-\u003einfo.members.clear();\n        conv-\u003einfo.members.emplace(username_);\n        conv-\u003einfo.members.emplace(request.from);\n        conv-\u003einfo.mode \u003d request.mode();\n        conv-\u003ereinvitePending \u003d true;\n```\nIf repository state later provides more authoritative metadata, it can still overwrite this, but the resurrected `ConvInfo` should not be based on the old tombstone.",
